Wash and dry produce. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(finely diced). Roughly chop
@Cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Zest half the @Lime{1}(zested and quartered).

Drain and roughly chop @Pulled Pork{8%ounce} into smaller pieces.

Heat @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
pork, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}, and
@salt{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until pork is warmed
through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Pork Ramen Stock Concentrate{1}, and
@water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook until broth has
thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer pork filling to a #medium bowl{}, leaving
broth behind. Cook until broth has reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat;
cover to keep warm.

== Pico de Gallo ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, lime zest, juice from
half the lime (whole lime for 4 servings), and @olive oil{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP
for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

== Tacos ==

Place @Flour Tortillas{6} on a clean work surface. Sprinkle one half of each
tortilla with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}; top with pork filling. Fold tortillas
in half to create tacos.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium heat. Add
tacos and cook until tortillas are crisped, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

== To Serve ==

Divide birria broth between small #serving bowls{}. If needed, return pan to
medium heat until broth is warmed through before serving.

Divide tacos between plates; serve with pico de gallo (draining first),
remaining lime wedges, and birria broth for dipping.